{"comments":"HSL color molecule - composition of Hue, Saturation, Lightness atoms.\n\nHSL (Hue, Saturation, Lightness) is a cylindrical color space that\nseparates color identity (hue) from color properties (saturation, lightness).\nThis makes it intuitive for color manipulation:\n\n- **Hue**: Position on the color wheel (0-359°)\n- **Saturation**: Color intensity/purity (0-100%)\n- **Lightness**: Light/dark level (0-100%)\n\n## Color Wheel Reference\n\n```\n  0°/360° = Red\n     60°  = Yellow\n    120°  = Green\n    180°  = Cyan\n    240°  = Blue\n    300°  = Magenta\n```\n\n## Lightness Behavior\n\n- At L=0%, any hue is black\n- At L=50%, colors are most vivid\n- At L=100%, any hue is white\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","HSL"],"HSL"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[86,32],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/HSL.purs","start":[86,1]},"title":"eqHSL"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","HSL"],"HSL"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[87,34],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/HSL.purs","start":[87,1]},"title":"ordHSL"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","HSL"],"HSL"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[90,21],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/HSL.purs","start":[89,1]},"title":"showHSL"}],"comments":"HSL color value - a molecule composed of three atoms.\n\nThis is a lawful composition: if Hue, Saturation, and Lightness are each\ncorrect (valid bounds, proper semantics), then HSL is correct by construction.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[84,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/HSL.purs","start":[80,1]},"title":"HSL"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create an HSL color from raw values.\n\nValues are normalized by the underlying atoms:\n- Hue clamps to 0-359 (use `rotate` for wrapping behavior)\n- Saturation clamps to 0-100\n- Lightness clamps to 0-100\n\n```purescript\nhsl 210 80 50  -- Ocean blue\nhsl 0 100 50   -- Pure red\nhsl 120 100 25 -- Dark green\n```\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","HSL"],"HSL"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[108,32],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/HSL.purs","start":[108,1]},"title":"hsl"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create from a record of raw values.\n**Explicitly named for backend persistence** - no conflicts with other color spaces.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[]